summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming the UN Charter and relevant resolutions, particularly 1373 (2001),
 Condemns in strongest terms the 11 March 2004 bomb attacks in Madrid, Spain, perpetrated by ETA, 
as a threat to peace and security; 
Expresses deepest sympathy to Spain, victims and their families; 
Urges States to cooperate in finding and bringing to justice the perpetrators, 
organizers and sponsors of the attack, under resolution 1373 (2001); 
Reiterates its determination to combat all forms of terrorism.
